ABIA State Governor, Okezie Ikpeazu, has issued a N10m cheque towards the education of the last son of the late representative of Aba North/South Federal Constituency, Ossy Prestige. Making the presentation during a town hall meeting, in Abiriba, Ikpeazu described the late Prestige as a close ally despite the difference in their political affiliations. The governor promised to play an active role in the burial of the late federal lawmaker. While receiving the cheque on behalf of the family, the member representing Aba Central State Constituency and Minority Leader of the Abia State House of Assembly, Abraham Oba, gave an assurance that the funds will be used for the purpose for which it was given. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 